cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.AI, cs.SI

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about automatic speech recognition (ASR) systems and recurrent neural network language models (RNNLM).
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a method to expand the vocabulary set of a pretrained RNNLM without retraining, which involves machine learning techniques.
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with speech recognition and language models.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper proposes a method to improve the performance of ASR systems using RNNLMs.
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes an unsupervised method to generate a list of out-of-shortlist (OOS) words to expand the vocabulary set, which involves information extraction techniques.
